Bubbaloo

==================

1. Introduction 
2. Install

==================

1. Introduction

A project for quantifying information filter bubbles.


2. Install

2.1 Dependencies

Bubbaloo depends on tor and pytorctl. 
Make sure that these are installed at your system.

- Tor : http://torproject.org/
- pytorctl : https://gitweb.torproject.org/pytorctl.git

2.2 Configuration

2.2.1 Tor

You can use the standard Tor bundle. Go to settings and enable control protocol (port 9051).
Also, in your torrc configuration file add 

StrictNodes 1 

2.2.2 Proxy

Bubbaloo uses wget to send requests through the tor network. To do that you should set up a proxy
(e.g. polipo) and set the proxy's parent to Tor's SOCKS proxy.

For more details : http://www.pps.jussieu.fr/~jch/software/polipo/tor.html